id: pm-ghf1
title: Reserved item-field name collisions are invisible to SDK lint/preflight/harness
description: "An extension can register an item field named like a reserved front-matter key (e.g. 'severity'; FRONT_MATTER_KEY_ORDER) and pass assertExtensionPreflight + createExtensionTestHarness green, but pm create/update rejects the field at runtime — a green package can brick create. Fix: export RESERVED_ITEM_FIELD_NAMES from the SDK and validate registered item-field keys in lintExtensionBlueprint/preflightExtension/harness. Found in 2026-07-02 audit (Lane B, pm-6vy7)."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[3]: audit-followup,schema,sdk
created_at: "2026-07-02T21:55:23.518Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-04T19:17:27.028Z"
author: claude-code-agent
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: "SDK lint, preflight, and test harness each flag reserved item-field name collisions from the shared reserved-key list; a drift test keeps that list in sync with constants."
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: medium
confidence: high
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-fpod,related,"2026-07-02T21:55:53.536Z",null,null
body: "## Context\nFound in the 2026-07-02 ecosystem audit (Lane B). An extension can register an item field whose name collides with a reserved front-matter key (e.g. 'severity', 'blocked_reason' — see FRONT_MATTER_KEY_ORDER) and still pass assertExtensionPreflight and createExtensionTestHarness green — but pm create/update rejects the field at runtime. A green package can brick create for its users.\n\n## Approach\nExport RESERVED_ITEM_FIELD_NAMES from the SDK (single source shared with the runtime validator) and validate registered item-field keys in lintExtensionBlueprint, preflightExtension, AND the test harness so the collision fails at authoring time with a rename hint. Known reserved names already bitten in the wild: severity (PR#150), blocked_reason (PR#367).\n\n## Definition of done\nA blueprint registering a reserved field name fails lint/preflight/harness with the same error code; SDK docs list the reserved names; runtime and SDK share one constant (no drift)."
